		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Erik Reece</span></strong> won the Sierra Club&rsquo;s David R. Brower Award for his book <em>Lost Mountain</em> (Riverhead Books), about strip mining in the Appalachians. He&rsquo;s also written a memoir about his Southern Baptist upbringing titled <em>An American Gospel: On Family, History, and the Kingdom of God</em> (Riverhead Books). He is a writer-in-residence at the University of Kentucky, and his work has appeared in <em>Harper&rsquo;s</em>, <em>Orion</em>, the <em>Nation</em>, and <em>Oxford American</em>.</p><a href="/contributors/erik-reece" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
	</div>
</div>

							</footer>
						</article>


